<@U89LVBDM2> welcome to the Digital Rebar Provision (DRP) <#C02L9P26Q|community>
Please insure you have started your DRP Endpoint service on the host first.  After the initial quickstart install, you must still start the service up

you can verify if the service is running on that host, with:
`ps -ef | grep -v grep | grep dr-provision`

the appropriate start command should have been sent to your shell/terminal when the installer ran - but it should be something like:
```sudo ./dr-provision --static-ip=<SOME IP ADDRESS> --file-root=`pwd`/drp-data/tftpboot --data-root=`pwd`/drp-data/digitalrebar --local-store="" --default-store=""```
When run from the directory that you performed the install in
the `<SOME IP ADDRESS>` portion should be an IP address on the node that is running `dr-provision` - and is the network that you will be doing provisioning activities on
It's running but command line ./drpcli bootenvs uploadiso ubuntu-16.04-install or ./drpcli bootenvs uploadiso centos-7-install Error: GET: bootenvs/ubuntu-16.04-install: Not Found
